1
00:00:04,037 --> 00:00:06,005
DRUGSTORE

2
00:00:06,006 --> 00:00:07,140
Welcome to our store.

3
00:00:11,778 --> 00:00:12,811
Welcome to our store.

4
00:00:12,812 --> 00:00:13,847
Hello.

5
00:00:14,681 --> 00:00:15,647
Hello, sir.

6
00:00:15,648 --> 00:00:16,616
Yes.

7
00:00:17,550 --> 00:00:18,618
You see...

8
00:00:20,920 --> 00:00:23,256
Your baby didn't eat that one?

9
00:00:25,125 --> 00:00:27,727
The baby is a picky eater. Really picky.

10
00:00:28,228 --> 00:00:30,363
He eats some foods but won't touch others.

11
00:00:33,933 --> 00:00:35,468
Can you wait here for a moment?

12
00:00:40,173 --> 00:00:41,341
Thank you for waiting.

13
00:00:42,075 --> 00:00:45,310
I was planning to give this to you
if I saw you again.

14
00:00:45,311 --> 00:00:47,947
I thought your baby might like it.

15
00:00:48,448 --> 00:00:50,315
ROUSONG

16
00:00:50,316 --> 00:00:51,717
<i>Rousong?</i>

17
00:00:51,718 --> 00:00:53,552
That's right, <i>rousong</i>.

18
00:00:53,553 --> 00:00:54,487
<i>Xiexie.</i>

19
00:00:55,455 --> 00:00:56,322
There you go.

20
00:00:58,758 --> 00:00:59,592
Oh?

21
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:08,168
THANK YOU FOR SHOPPING WITH US.
PLEASE GIVE THIS TO YOUR BABY.

22
00:01:08,735 --> 00:01:09,869
Thank you so much.

23
00:01:18,945 --> 00:01:20,212
You're such a weirdo.

24
00:01:20,213 --> 00:01:22,381
It was a favor Volunteer asked,

25
00:01:22,382 --> 00:01:25,685
but you're taking care of him
like he's your own kid.

26
00:01:36,729 --> 00:01:39,866
FOUR DAYS AGO

27
00:01:43,636 --> 00:01:44,704
Who is this child?

28
00:01:45,271 --> 00:01:46,606
He's a child of someone I know.

29
00:01:47,240 --> 00:01:50,210
Look after him for a week,
and I'll come pick him up.

30
00:01:50,977 --> 00:01:52,145
Just don't take him outside.

31
00:01:53,947 --> 00:01:54,781
Understood.

32
00:01:56,683 --> 00:01:59,318
But... what should I do
about my job at the factory?

33
00:01:59,319 --> 00:02:01,054
You're quitting anyway.

34
00:02:02,856 --> 00:02:06,126
But now you can finally go home
through a proper channel.

35
00:02:07,861 --> 00:02:11,431
I'm telling you, I'm giving you
a passport for free.

36
00:02:12,499 --> 00:02:13,399
You understand, don't you?

37
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:22,375
If you could help me with this,

38
00:02:25,979 --> 00:02:27,380
I'd really appreciate it.

39
00:02:28,481 --> 00:02:30,917
THE HARASHIMAS - KIDNAPPING
SHUN: 1 YEAR AND 2 MONTHS OLD

40
00:02:36,089 --> 00:02:39,024
KOJI: GAMBLING ISSUES
DEBT: 2.5 MILLION YEN (MULTIPLE SOURCES)

41
00:02:39,025 --> 00:02:42,028
SOLD CITIZENSHIP FOR 1 MILLION YEN
JAPANESE CITIZENSHIP - PROFITABLE

42
00:03:09,022 --> 00:03:14,127
DAY FIVE SINCE THE KIDNAPPING

43
00:03:29,943 --> 00:03:33,846
Allow us to expand the target area
of our investigation a bit further.

44
00:03:35,148 --> 00:03:37,350
Expand the target area further?

45
00:03:38,685 --> 00:03:40,385
SOLD CITIZENSHIP TO ALISAH
YUKI'S FORMER COLLEAGUE AT THE CLUB

46
00:03:40,386 --> 00:03:42,455
No ransom demand has been made yet.

47
00:03:45,425 --> 00:03:47,860
What on earth could the kidnapper want?

48
00:03:48,361 --> 00:03:50,963
ALISAH

49
00:03:50,964 --> 00:03:52,931
INTERROGATION ROOM

50
00:03:52,932 --> 00:03:55,500
You know Koji Harashima, don't you,

51
00:03:55,501 --> 00:03:56,502
Alisah?

52
00:03:57,637 --> 00:03:59,305
He's one of our regulars at the club.

53
00:04:00,840 --> 00:04:01,774
Alisah,

54
00:04:02,542 --> 00:04:04,611
did you have feelings for Mr. Harashima?

55
00:04:05,511 --> 00:04:06,613
Why would I want him?

56
00:04:07,447 --> 00:04:09,249
Or perhaps you were jealous of Yuki?

57
00:04:09,749 --> 00:04:12,417
That's why you wanted to harass
the family a little.

58
00:04:12,418 --> 00:04:13,353
Isn't that right?

59
00:04:19,425 --> 00:04:21,594
Even if that's true,
targeting their baby is...

60
00:04:22,795 --> 00:04:23,796
What do you mean, their baby?

61
00:04:24,430 --> 00:04:26,898
If you know something,
you'd better tell us now.

62
00:04:26,899 --> 00:04:27,934
I don't know anything.

63
00:04:29,068 --> 00:04:32,471
Someone wanted to buy citizenship,
so I just sold it to him.

64
00:04:32,472 --> 00:04:33,472
That's all, really.

65
00:04:33,473 --> 00:04:35,541
Can you describe what he looked like?

66
00:04:36,442 --> 00:04:40,313
He spoke various languages on the phone,
but I don't know much about anything.

67
00:04:40,813 --> 00:04:43,682
I don't know what the buyer would do
with the citizenship,

68
00:04:43,683 --> 00:04:45,585
and I'm not even interested.

69
00:04:51,391 --> 00:04:52,925
Welcome to our store.

70
00:04:53,893 --> 00:04:54,761
Good afternoon.

71
00:04:56,763 --> 00:04:58,730
The baby really enjoyed the <i>rousong</i>
you gave me.

72
00:04:58,731 --> 00:05:00,099
He ate a lot of it.

73
00:05:01,034 --> 00:05:04,069
Really? He did? That makes me so happy.

74
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:05,171
Thank you so much.

75
00:05:05,905 --> 00:05:07,440
You're welcome.

76
00:05:08,441 --> 00:05:10,977
By the way, what's your baby's name?

77
00:05:14,213 --> 00:05:16,349
It's... Yuhang.

78
00:05:17,917 --> 00:05:19,018
Wuhang?

79
00:05:21,321 --> 00:05:22,722
What a cute name!

80
00:05:23,456 --> 00:05:24,290
Thank you.

81
00:05:24,791 --> 00:05:26,125
You're welcome.

82
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:29,394
If you need anything, let me know.

83
00:05:29,395 --> 00:05:30,296
I will.

84
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:35,735
Wuhang.

85
00:05:50,116 --> 00:05:52,617
Manager, it's happening.

86
00:05:52,618 --> 00:05:54,220
The diaper shoplifter is here.

87
00:05:54,821 --> 00:05:57,456
We're letting him go this time, right?

88
00:05:57,457 --> 00:05:59,425
That's right. Here he is.

89
00:06:01,060 --> 00:06:04,796
What we're after this time
is to uncover the group behind.

90
00:06:04,797 --> 00:06:06,031
I'd appreciate your cooperation.

91
00:06:06,032 --> 00:06:07,232
No problem.

92
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:09,101
We'll cover the damages.

93
00:06:09,102 --> 00:06:10,336
Thank you.

94
00:06:11,637 --> 00:06:14,039
Manager, smile,
or he'll notice something's up.

95
00:06:14,040 --> 00:06:15,108
Okay.

96
00:06:29,722 --> 00:06:31,657
- Don't do that.
- Move.

97
00:06:32,859 --> 00:06:35,026
- You have to pay money.
- Hey!

98
00:06:35,027 --> 00:06:36,763
Son of a bitch!

99
00:06:37,263 --> 00:06:38,664
Sir!

100
00:06:39,265 --> 00:06:40,299
Stop!

101
00:06:46,205 --> 00:06:48,006
Don't resist. This is the police!

102
00:06:48,007 --> 00:06:48,974
Fuck.

103
00:06:48,975 --> 00:06:50,276
Police?

104
00:06:50,877 --> 00:06:52,310
Kana, call for backup now!

105
00:06:52,311 --> 00:06:53,346
Yes!

106
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:55,247
Help me!

107
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,849
Miss Koda? Why?

108
00:06:57,884 --> 00:06:58,717
We're not letting him go?

109
00:06:58,718 --> 00:07:01,387
I'm really sorry,
but something unexpected happened.

110
00:07:01,888 --> 00:07:02,754
Fuck!

111
00:07:02,755 --> 00:07:04,424
Are you all right, sir?

112
00:07:08,194 --> 00:07:11,464
<i>GOMOKU</i> RICE

113
00:08:19,098 --> 00:08:20,633
Well done, Koda.

114
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:26,638
To be honest, I've always thought
you were someone with some major flaws.

115
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:28,874
But I repent. Please forgive me.

116
00:08:28,875 --> 00:08:29,909
No worries.

117
00:08:31,244 --> 00:08:32,544
What's wrong?

118
00:08:32,545 --> 00:08:35,547
You did a great job,
arresting the culprit successfully

119
00:08:35,548 --> 00:08:36,449
without anyone getting hurt.

120
00:08:37,450 --> 00:08:38,618
- Look at you.
- Sure.

121
00:08:39,118 --> 00:08:40,953
But it wasn't me who caught him.

122
00:08:42,255 --> 00:08:43,089
What do you mean?

123
00:08:45,324 --> 00:08:46,893
Um... It's nothing.

124
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:50,630
All right. Then finish up your paperwork.

125
00:08:51,597 --> 00:08:53,132
<i>Gomoku</i> rice sounds good.

126
00:08:54,033 --> 00:08:55,067
Oh, I want to lose weight!

127
00:08:55,568 --> 00:08:56,535
Oof.

128
00:08:56,536 --> 00:08:58,104
<i>GOMOKU</i> RICE

129
00:09:02,575 --> 00:09:04,075
- Hey!
- Yes?

130
00:09:04,076 --> 00:09:08,247
DAY SIX SINCE THE KIDNAPPING

131
00:09:08,948 --> 00:09:10,683
Come on, take it quickly.

132
00:09:19,158 --> 00:09:22,160
Hey, you over there!
Come and help out here.

133
00:09:22,161 --> 00:09:23,329
Sure.

134
00:09:28,267 --> 00:09:30,803
One, two, three.

135
00:09:32,471 --> 00:09:34,339
- Wang.
- Hey.

136
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:36,341
Take this garbage out of here.

137
00:09:36,342 --> 00:09:38,077
Sure.

138
00:09:42,515 --> 00:09:44,717
Careful, it’s high here.
Don’t hit your head.

139
00:09:45,618 --> 00:09:47,186
Push it in.

140
00:09:48,454 --> 00:09:49,455
Further in.

141
00:09:49,956 --> 00:09:52,724
SEICHO CHEMICALS

142
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:55,360
Do you know which size you're looking for?

143
00:09:55,361 --> 00:09:57,495
The baby's backside is...

144
00:09:57,496 --> 00:09:58,563
SEICHO CHEMICALS

145
00:09:58,564 --> 00:09:59,966
...about this size.

146
00:10:06,772 --> 00:10:09,642
- Is it okay if we borrow your umbrellas?
- Sure, go find it yourself.

147
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,167
Sir?

148
00:10:37,436 --> 00:10:39,905
Wait. Stop. Sir, stop.

149
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:41,340
Wait.

150
00:10:42,074 --> 00:10:44,543
It's all right. It's all right.

151
00:10:45,044 --> 00:10:45,878
Okay?

152
00:10:48,014 --> 00:10:48,848
Okay?

153
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:53,019
I brought this.

154
00:10:54,053 --> 00:10:56,188
You left it the other day.

155
00:10:56,856 --> 00:10:57,757
Look.

156
00:11:02,361 --> 00:11:04,729
Also, I'd like you to have this.

157
00:11:04,730 --> 00:11:06,731
FOR FOREIGN RESIDENTS RESIDING IN TOKYO

158
00:11:06,732 --> 00:11:08,067
It's tough for people who've come
from overseas

159
00:11:08,567 --> 00:11:10,403
to rebuild their lives here.

160
00:11:10,903 --> 00:11:15,675
And raising a baby on top of that
is incredibly challenging.

161
00:11:18,277 --> 00:11:20,479
And one more thing.

162
00:11:23,482 --> 00:11:26,986
If there's something
you desperately need help with,

163
00:11:27,887 --> 00:11:28,921
please contact me.

164
00:11:35,728 --> 00:11:36,562
You know what?

165
00:11:39,899 --> 00:11:41,333
To be honest,

166
00:11:42,601 --> 00:11:45,404
I haven't quite figured it out yet.

167
00:11:46,138 --> 00:11:47,606
I can't tell if you're a good person

168
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:50,776
or a bad person.

169
00:11:53,345 --> 00:11:54,346
But...

170
00:11:56,082 --> 00:11:57,950
When I saw you at the store,

171
00:12:00,519 --> 00:12:03,122
I thought you must be a good father.

172
00:12:09,061 --> 00:12:10,730
Take good care of Wuhang.

173
00:12:12,998 --> 00:12:14,300
Cherish him.

174
00:12:20,206 --> 00:12:21,974
See you then.

175
00:12:33,052 --> 00:12:38,090
SERGEANT MARI KODA

176
00:12:41,260 --> 00:12:43,195
You're such a good boy...

177
00:12:45,498 --> 00:12:46,432
Yuhang.

178
00:13:04,016 --> 00:13:06,317
<i>I was just thinking
about the boy's parents.</i>

179
00:13:06,318 --> 00:13:08,254
Probably,

180
00:13:08,954 --> 00:13:13,325
they never imagined facing an incident
like this in Japan today.

181
00:13:16,095 --> 00:13:19,097
Are you saying Shun was kidnapped
because of me?

182
00:13:19,098 --> 00:13:20,698
I thought I would be safe

183
00:13:20,699 --> 00:13:23,869
if I married a Japanese man
and became Japanese.

184
00:13:26,605 --> 00:13:30,176
<i>Someone wanted to buy citizenship,
so I just sold it to him.</i>

185
00:13:30,676 --> 00:13:34,547
I don't know what the buyer would do
with the citizenship.

186
00:14:02,808 --> 00:14:03,842
BANH MI

187
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:04,877
Excuse me.

188
00:14:05,644 --> 00:14:08,247
Can I have one <i>banh mi</i> and...

189
00:14:13,586 --> 00:14:17,422
There's chicken liver pâté,

190
00:14:17,423 --> 00:14:20,593
along with tangy pickled
daikon radish and carrot.

191
00:14:23,629 --> 00:14:24,530
<i>When you think about it,</i>

192
00:14:25,931 --> 00:14:27,566
people and food culture

193
00:14:28,901 --> 00:14:32,705
have crossed country borders
and transcended boundaries.

194
00:14:34,473 --> 00:14:38,277
And they continue to evolve
after reaching their destinations.

195
00:14:53,459 --> 00:14:54,460
Mr. Yanagi.

196
00:14:55,995 --> 00:14:57,029
Can I talk to you?

197
00:14:57,529 --> 00:15:00,532
Can you set up a dragnet
at Kanto and Tohoku ports and airports?

198
00:15:02,134 --> 00:15:03,868
You're just an interpreter.

199
00:15:03,869 --> 00:15:05,371
Do you understand what you're saying?

200
00:15:05,871 --> 00:15:07,840
I'm sorry, but we don't have time.

201
00:15:12,111 --> 00:15:15,648
Your departure date is set.
You're leaving tomorrow morning.

202
00:15:16,615 --> 00:15:18,250
- Tomorrow morning?
- Tomorrow morning?

203
00:15:19,151 --> 00:15:20,886
Why at ports and airports?

204
00:15:21,654 --> 00:15:25,023
The warrant should target
Koji Harashima, his wife Yuki,

205
00:15:25,024 --> 00:15:26,458
and their son Shun.

206
00:15:27,526 --> 00:15:28,359
What?

207
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:31,563
The father sold his citizenship to Alisah,

208
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:34,533
and Alisah sold it to some foreigner.

209
00:15:35,100 --> 00:15:35,934
It's very likely

210
00:15:35,935 --> 00:15:38,871
that they will apply for passports
using Harashima's citizenship.

211
00:15:39,438 --> 00:15:40,572
JAPAN PASSPORT

212
00:15:45,477 --> 00:15:47,745
KOJI HARASHIMA

213
00:15:47,746 --> 00:15:48,646
YUKI HARASHIMA

214
00:15:48,647 --> 00:15:50,549
<i>He also sold his family register,</i>

215
00:15:51,116 --> 00:15:54,753
<i>which means the citizenships
of the entire family were sold.</i>

216
00:15:58,490 --> 00:15:59,792
Yuki...

217
00:16:03,462 --> 00:16:04,929
<i>They were the perfect target</i>

218
00:16:04,930 --> 00:16:07,766
<i>because he had issues
and his wife was originally Chinese.</i>

219
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:11,537
<i>It's easy to find a couple who can pose
as Mr. and Mrs. Harashima.</i>

220
00:16:12,604 --> 00:16:16,342
<i>If Shun is with them,
they're the perfect family in disguise.</i>

221
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:21,847
Passports can be obtained
with imposters using proper documents.

222
00:16:22,348 --> 00:16:24,183
Language won't be a hindrance.

223
00:16:25,351 --> 00:16:27,051
Shun could easily leave Japan

224
00:16:27,052 --> 00:16:30,422
with his fake parents
through the proper channels.

225
00:16:31,056 --> 00:16:34,192
Given that there are flights
to and from the mainland,

226
00:16:34,193 --> 00:16:36,996
and the security is lax,
West Ibaraki Airport is likely...

227
00:16:40,232 --> 00:16:42,568
I'm making an exception this time.
You come along.

228
00:16:43,569 --> 00:16:44,403
Yes, sir.

229
00:16:47,973 --> 00:16:51,243
JAPAN PASSPORT

230
00:16:55,881 --> 00:16:57,882
SHUN HARASHIMA

231
00:16:57,883 --> 00:17:00,285
Take the baby to the mainland
and hand him over

232
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:03,188
to the person waiting at the airport.

233
00:17:03,989 --> 00:17:06,759
Is the person waiting at the airport
this boy's parent?

234
00:17:08,193 --> 00:17:09,994
- What will happen to this boy?
- Hey.

235
00:17:09,995 --> 00:17:13,832
I wonder what will happen to your folks
if you ask any more questions.

236
00:17:16,402 --> 00:17:20,773
SHUN HARASHIMA

237
00:17:22,007 --> 00:17:25,309
DAY SEVEN SINCE THE KIDNAPPING

238
00:17:25,310 --> 00:17:26,578
Let's go.

239
00:17:30,682 --> 00:17:31,984
Let's go outside.

240
00:17:42,294 --> 00:17:44,296
It's been ten years.

241
00:17:44,797 --> 00:17:48,400
I worked tirelessly in Japan
to pay for my sister's hospital bill.

242
00:17:50,202 --> 00:17:52,604
But while doing so,
I lost the means to go home.

243
00:17:53,939 --> 00:17:57,543
But it's all coming to an end finally.

244
00:17:59,344 --> 00:18:00,813
How about you?

245
00:18:01,313 --> 00:18:03,215
Do you have any family waiting for you?

246
00:18:08,921 --> 00:18:13,425
WEST IBARAKI AIRPORT

247
00:18:16,228 --> 00:18:17,896
Thank you so much.

248
00:18:24,470 --> 00:18:26,437
DEPARTURES

249
00:18:26,438 --> 00:18:27,372
Hello.

250
00:18:28,340 --> 00:18:31,043
Three of us have just arrived.

251
00:18:32,177 --> 00:18:33,745
Thank you for everything.

252
00:18:35,214 --> 00:18:39,384
Hey! Where are you going?
We need to check in.

253
00:18:40,752 --> 00:18:43,655
I'm going to go change his diaper.
Or would you do it?

254
00:18:44,256 --> 00:18:47,659
There's no way I'm doing that.
Just hurry up then.

255
00:18:51,363 --> 00:18:52,998
Dad’s changing his diaper.

256
00:19:29,535 --> 00:19:31,537
Thank you very much.
Let me take your luggage.

257
00:19:34,206 --> 00:19:35,040
And here's your boarding pass.

258
00:19:36,742 --> 00:19:37,910
Have a great flight!

259
00:19:41,213 --> 00:19:42,147
Excuse me.

260
00:19:43,882 --> 00:19:45,184
Can I talk to you?

261
00:19:50,522 --> 00:19:52,290
Who the heck are you people?

262
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:56,360
Do you mind if we take a look
at your passport for a moment?

263
00:19:56,361 --> 00:19:58,563
Hey, stop. Give it back.

264
00:19:58,564 --> 00:20:00,932
- This is Yuki Harashima's passport.
- Give back my passport!

265
00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:02,401
Where are the man and the baby?

266
00:20:07,806 --> 00:20:09,208
- Seal all exits.
- Yes, sir.

267
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:08,834
Excuse me.

268
00:21:09,334 --> 00:21:10,167
Yes?

269
00:21:10,168 --> 00:21:12,804
I want to see someone who works here.

270
00:21:15,307 --> 00:21:17,809
Do you know the name of the person?

271
00:21:18,310 --> 00:21:22,080
Um... She has a green-colored head.

272
00:21:22,914 --> 00:21:23,749
Excuse me?

273
00:21:27,286 --> 00:21:30,988
It's you? What brings you here?

274
00:21:30,989 --> 00:21:32,624
You surprised me.

275
00:21:34,626 --> 00:21:36,161
Oh?

276
00:21:37,029 --> 00:21:37,863
Unbelievable.

277
00:21:38,530 --> 00:21:42,567
So, this boy is your Wuhang?

278
00:21:45,137 --> 00:21:47,773
Hello, sweetie. Nice to meet you.

279
00:21:51,109 --> 00:21:53,278
I... I don't know his name.

280
00:21:57,149 --> 00:22:01,386
Don't the police know his real name?

281
00:22:05,357 --> 00:22:06,425
Hello?

282
00:22:07,626 --> 00:22:08,694
Yes, that's right.

283
00:22:09,828 --> 00:22:10,662
What?

284
00:22:13,398 --> 00:22:14,232
Are you serious?

285
00:22:15,567 --> 00:22:18,302
One of our sergeants, Koda,
has secured him.

286
00:22:18,303 --> 00:22:19,371
He's with us now.

287
00:22:19,871 --> 00:22:20,706
This way, please.

288
00:22:48,533 --> 00:22:51,703
Thank you... Thank you...

289
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:02,613
<i>The man's name is Wang Jianbin.</i>

290
00:23:02,614 --> 00:23:05,117
<i>He's 48 years old
and from Fujian Province.</i>

291
00:23:06,118 --> 00:23:09,254
<i>He came to Japan ten years ago
under the Technical Intern Program</i>

292
00:23:10,155 --> 00:23:11,656
<i>and has overstayed his visa.</i>

293
00:23:14,259 --> 00:23:17,462
The woman, Liu Xiao, also from Fujian,
has a similar background.

294
00:23:22,033 --> 00:23:24,236
They are not married to each other.

295
00:23:24,970 --> 00:23:27,606
In fact, they only met about ten days ago.

296
00:23:30,308 --> 00:23:32,544
Wang has remained silent
during questioning,

297
00:23:33,044 --> 00:23:34,846
leaving too many unknowns at this point.

298
00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:40,352
The grounds for his arrest

299
00:23:40,852 --> 00:23:43,255
were suspicion of kidnapping a minor, correct?

300
00:23:45,190 --> 00:23:46,224
That makes sense,

301
00:23:47,426 --> 00:23:49,995
considering he was with a child
who had been kidnapped.

302
00:23:50,862 --> 00:23:54,266
But he told me he didn't even know
the baby's name.

303
00:23:54,933 --> 00:23:57,135
Isn't it odd if he took him
from their home?

304
00:23:58,570 --> 00:24:01,071
And since he was overstaying,

305
00:24:01,072 --> 00:24:04,109
he must've known he would be detained
if he went to the police.

306
00:24:05,477 --> 00:24:07,845
There's definitely something unnatural
about it.

307
00:24:07,846 --> 00:24:08,780
Yes.

308
00:24:10,315 --> 00:24:12,784
He's such a nice person, you know.

309
00:24:14,119 --> 00:24:15,787
I just can't believe he's the kidnapper.

310
00:24:16,288 --> 00:24:18,390
We need to hear the truth from him.

311
00:24:23,361 --> 00:24:24,663
Wuhang...

312
00:24:27,232 --> 00:24:28,834
I wonder why he called the baby

313
00:24:29,768 --> 00:24:31,736
by that name with so much affection.

314
00:24:43,715 --> 00:24:44,883
By the way, Arikeeno,

315
00:24:46,585 --> 00:24:49,754
are you the one interpreting
during his questioning?

316
00:24:50,388 --> 00:24:51,690
Yes, probably.

317
00:24:53,558 --> 00:24:54,558
I want to ask you a favor.

318
00:24:54,559 --> 00:24:57,362
You told me about an online
bulletin board in China.

319
00:24:57,863 --> 00:25:02,099
Would you mind searching the site
to see if there's any information

320
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:03,401
about a missing child named Wuhang?

321
00:25:04,603 --> 00:25:06,805
That's completely impossible.

322
00:25:07,706 --> 00:25:10,408
Finding a child among the countless
missing children

323
00:25:11,209 --> 00:25:13,077
is like looking for a needle in a desert.

324
00:25:13,078 --> 00:25:14,479
Still, I want to look for him.

325
00:25:16,081 --> 00:25:19,684
If we give up, nothing would be uncovered.

326
00:25:21,553 --> 00:25:23,622
Please. Would you look for him?

327
00:25:25,423 --> 00:25:29,394
I don't think we can find him
because we have too little information.

328
00:25:30,161 --> 00:25:31,296
But we try anyway, right?

329
00:25:31,796 --> 00:25:32,664
Yes.

330
00:25:37,536 --> 00:25:39,570
Here you are, my mighty helpers!

331
00:25:39,571 --> 00:25:41,839
Thank you for coming.

332
00:25:41,840 --> 00:25:42,807
Why are they here?

333
00:25:43,842 --> 00:25:45,744
I asked them to come here to help.

334
00:25:46,344 --> 00:25:49,380
I'm so happy
you thought to ask me for help.

335
00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:53,317
Work requiring patience and reasoning
is highly rewarding for interpreters.

336
00:25:53,318 --> 00:25:57,522
Mr. Arikino, you should rely on us more
when you need help.

337
00:25:59,257 --> 00:26:01,358
Why involve me after my day's work?

338
00:26:01,359 --> 00:26:04,195
We're great at checking
all the details, aren't we?

339
00:26:05,964 --> 00:26:08,132
All right then. Let's do it.

340
00:26:08,133 --> 00:26:09,166
Yes, ma'am.

341
00:26:09,167 --> 00:26:10,468
Arikeeno, go ahead.

342
00:26:10,969 --> 00:26:13,071
All right, so...

343
00:26:13,972 --> 00:26:18,008
I'm emailing you the website name
along with Mr. Wang's information.

344
00:26:18,009 --> 00:26:20,278
WUHENG WANG, REGISTRATION INFORMATION

345
00:26:26,251 --> 00:26:29,788
Wang... Wang... There are Wangs everywhere.

346
00:26:30,522 --> 00:26:32,690
It's 8% of all last names in China,

347
00:26:32,691 --> 00:26:35,293
making it one of the most common.

348
00:26:43,268 --> 00:26:44,336
Miss Koda...

349
00:26:51,676 --> 00:26:54,479
Could he possibly be Yuhang
instead of Wuhang?

350
00:26:58,717 --> 00:26:59,884
Yuhang.

351
00:27:01,219 --> 00:27:02,053
Wuhang...

352
00:27:03,588 --> 00:27:05,423
It's... Yuhang.

353
00:27:06,157 --> 00:27:09,027
It was Yu... You mean, Yu...

354
00:27:09,527 --> 00:27:10,462
I'm sorry. You may be right.

355
00:27:11,029 --> 00:27:13,932
Then, select a combination
of Chinese characters from here

356
00:27:14,799 --> 00:27:17,167
and search within Fujian Province.

357
00:27:17,168 --> 00:27:18,502
- Okay.
- I'm so sorry.

358
00:27:18,503 --> 00:27:19,437
It's okay.

359
00:27:20,772 --> 00:27:21,706
Let's see...

360
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:25,944
Mr. Kurosu, Mr. Arikino wants us
to use this for the search.

361
00:27:27,545 --> 00:27:30,114
I'm so sorry,
but it might have been Yuhang.

362
00:27:30,115 --> 00:27:31,282
Rain...

363
00:27:32,784 --> 00:27:33,618
Feather...

364
00:27:36,755 --> 00:27:38,023
Word...

365
00:27:46,097 --> 00:27:48,333
YURI KIYOMIYA

366
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:58,109
RUSSIAN, VIETNAMESE

367
00:27:58,677 --> 00:27:59,911
Could it be...

368
00:28:01,413 --> 00:28:02,347
this child?

369
00:28:05,550 --> 00:28:07,652
Which child? Which one?

370
00:28:18,363 --> 00:28:21,232
- I'm here, sir.
- Here you are.

371
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:25,804
Why would you want me to sit in
on the questioning?

372
00:28:28,673 --> 00:28:31,642
This time,
regarding the citizenship trades,

373
00:28:31,643 --> 00:28:34,612
Arikino and Shakuno have contributed
greatly to our efforts.

374
00:28:37,015 --> 00:28:38,482
And most importantly,

375
00:28:38,483 --> 00:28:41,820
we succeeded in securing the child
and arresting the man.

376
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:43,588
We owed it to you.

377
00:28:47,325 --> 00:28:48,693
Thank you, sir.

378
00:28:52,664 --> 00:28:53,765
But actually,

379
00:28:54,632 --> 00:28:57,502
we discovered something
after investigating it all day.

380
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:06,511
Who was it that kidnapped the child
and brought him to you?

381
00:29:26,865 --> 00:29:28,266
Are you going to keep silent?

382
00:29:40,912 --> 00:29:43,148
"I cannot betray Volunteer."

383
00:30:02,433 --> 00:30:05,136
"He was helping me get home

384
00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:07,972
when I had no money and no visa.

385
00:30:09,107 --> 00:30:10,975
He even gave me a passport for free.

386
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:17,482
But I ended up betraying him
because I came to the police."

387
00:30:22,153 --> 00:30:23,054
That's not true.

388
00:30:26,357 --> 00:30:29,694
It was Volunteer who betrayed you.

389
00:30:35,233 --> 00:30:37,035
Volunteer betrayed me?

390
00:30:39,337 --> 00:30:40,505
You were being used

391
00:30:44,209 --> 00:30:46,144
by the kidnapper.

392
00:30:48,012 --> 00:30:51,516
I was used? What are you saying?

393
00:30:55,386 --> 00:30:56,955
Let me share my speculation

394
00:30:59,757 --> 00:31:01,059
about Volunteer's scheme.

395
00:31:02,861 --> 00:31:05,363
He might have been planning

396
00:31:06,564 --> 00:31:08,199
to sell all three of you.

397
00:31:10,702 --> 00:31:13,738
That's not true. You're lying.

398
00:31:18,243 --> 00:31:21,412
You're trying to protect Volunteer,

399
00:31:23,047 --> 00:31:24,849
but he's not a good person at all.

400
00:31:27,118 --> 00:31:28,353
<i>He is a devil.</i>

401
00:31:35,360 --> 00:31:37,328
You came to the police

402
00:31:38,263 --> 00:31:39,864
because you sensed something wasn't right.

403
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:49,707
You know what I noticed about the baby?

404
00:31:53,211 --> 00:31:55,880
He was missing for nearly a week,

405
00:31:56,547 --> 00:31:57,582
but he has no injury.

406
00:31:58,483 --> 00:32:00,184
He doesn't have diaper rash,

407
00:32:01,252 --> 00:32:03,221
and he's even gained a little weight.

408
00:32:04,689 --> 00:32:09,060
The doctor at the hospital said
he's in very good health.

409
00:32:13,898 --> 00:32:15,266
Are you...

410
00:32:17,669 --> 00:32:19,737
looking for Yuhang?

411
00:32:23,408 --> 00:32:24,676
How did you know?

412
00:32:35,186 --> 00:32:38,823
I considered the possibility,
and we searched together.

413
00:32:50,335 --> 00:32:51,436
"Yuhang."

414
00:32:53,104 --> 00:32:57,041
WANG YUHANG

415
00:33:13,925 --> 00:33:16,527
I came to Japan ten years ago

416
00:33:19,430 --> 00:33:24,936
to earn money so I could look for my son.

417
00:33:32,343 --> 00:33:36,347
I've been sending money to my wife
all this time.

418
00:33:41,786 --> 00:33:46,923
I was afraid Volunteer would harm my wife

419
00:33:46,924 --> 00:33:53,731
if I revealed anything about him.

420
00:34:00,738 --> 00:34:02,473
My wife and I have been searching

421
00:34:03,875 --> 00:34:07,912
for our son all this time.

422
00:34:13,618 --> 00:34:15,119
Searching for him was

423
00:34:18,289 --> 00:34:20,858
the only reason we kept living.

424
00:34:26,130 --> 00:34:30,001
I'm sure he's forgotten about us by now.

425
00:34:38,242 --> 00:34:41,646
And my visa expired long time ago.

426
00:34:45,016 --> 00:34:47,285
My wife is still searching for him.

427
00:34:50,922 --> 00:34:52,590
I'm not sure

428
00:34:54,792 --> 00:35:00,865
if Yuhang is still alive or not.

429
00:35:40,872 --> 00:35:44,642
Alisah says she's sold citizenships
of more than ten people to Volunteer.

430
00:35:45,476 --> 00:35:47,577
Volunteer targets East Asian individuals

431
00:35:47,578 --> 00:35:51,548
who look Japanese and are overstaying.

432
00:35:51,549 --> 00:35:53,283
He claims that his priority

433
00:35:53,284 --> 00:35:57,088
is helping those in need of money
who have no one to rely on in Japan.

434
00:35:57,588 --> 00:35:59,624
He makes it sound like it's charity work.

435
00:36:00,191 --> 00:36:05,496
I bet so many people who are overstaying
have fallen victim to him.

436
00:36:06,230 --> 00:36:07,298
And listen to this.

437
00:36:07,798 --> 00:36:11,434
Do you know what Volunteer said
when Liu thanked him

438
00:36:11,435 --> 00:36:13,538
for helping her as a fellow countryman?

439
00:36:14,739 --> 00:36:18,475
"I'm not your fellow countryman.
I'm Japanese." That's what he said.

440
00:36:18,476 --> 00:36:19,644
What the...

441
00:36:21,045 --> 00:36:23,748
I'm not sure what he really meant by that.

442
00:36:27,552 --> 00:36:30,421
The victims of trafficking
lead miserable lives.

443
00:36:31,189 --> 00:36:32,956
Their freedom is taken away.

444
00:36:32,957 --> 00:36:34,691
And they lose the right

445
00:36:34,692 --> 00:36:37,228
to self-determination
over their lives and their bodies.

446
00:36:37,728 --> 00:36:39,297
Their lives could be taken from them.

447
00:36:40,498 --> 00:36:43,467
But when overstayers are the target,

448
00:36:43,968 --> 00:36:46,971
it's difficult for the police
to take action.

449
00:36:48,606 --> 00:36:50,374
They're not just "overstayers."

450
00:36:53,844 --> 00:36:57,615
Each one of those people is a human being.

451
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:02,320
It's heinous to take advantage
of their desire to go home,

452
00:37:02,820 --> 00:37:07,024
use the means to go home as bait,
and sell them to criminal groups.

453
00:37:08,326 --> 00:37:12,163
We can't turn a blind eye
to such human trafficking in Japan.

454
00:37:12,663 --> 00:37:13,798
Koda is right.

455
00:37:14,365 --> 00:37:16,267
If this is true,
we can't let them get away with it.

456
00:37:17,335 --> 00:37:19,603
Shakuno, submit a report to headquarters.

457
00:37:19,604 --> 00:37:20,737
Yes, sir.

458
00:37:20,738 --> 00:37:23,541
We'll make going after Volunteer
our top priority.

459
00:37:24,108 --> 00:37:25,009
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

460
00:37:35,886 --> 00:37:39,290
He won't be prosecuted on the charge
of kidnapping a minor.

461
00:37:41,592 --> 00:37:42,927
But he will probably be sentenced

462
00:37:43,894 --> 00:37:47,064
to two years of imprisonment
with three years of probation.

463
00:37:48,666 --> 00:37:53,037
But in the end, he will be deported.

464
00:37:57,208 --> 00:37:58,242
I understand.

465
00:38:14,425 --> 00:38:17,495
Wang Jianbin is on his way
to the Kasumigaseki detention center.

466
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:26,737
Arikeeno, will you interpret this
and tell him?

467
00:38:28,072 --> 00:38:28,939
Please.

468
00:38:32,043 --> 00:38:32,910
Excuse me.

469
00:38:34,245 --> 00:38:35,078
What is it?

470
00:38:35,079 --> 00:38:38,082
I want to explain the detention period
to him.

471
00:38:40,751 --> 00:38:41,786
He has my permission.

472
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:43,254
Understood.

473
00:38:47,358 --> 00:38:49,126
She asked me to pass along
a message to you.

474
00:38:52,430 --> 00:38:55,832
You tried to protect the boy,

475
00:38:55,833 --> 00:38:58,736
even sacrificing your chance to go home.

476
00:38:59,337 --> 00:39:00,837
That was because

477
00:39:00,838 --> 00:39:04,041
you saw glimpses of your son
in that boy, didn't you?

478
00:39:08,479 --> 00:39:12,750
Yuhang protected you.

479
00:39:15,019 --> 00:39:18,889
You and Yuhang still have a chance
to reunite in this lifetime.

480
00:39:19,890 --> 00:39:22,827
So please keep living.

481
00:39:31,335 --> 00:39:32,670
<i>Daddy!</i>

482
00:39:35,005 --> 00:39:36,540
Daddy!

483
00:40:15,279 --> 00:40:17,081
It's remarkable that you figured out

484
00:40:18,315 --> 00:40:22,253
the kidnapper's intent
was to take the baby out of Japan.

485
00:40:24,588 --> 00:40:27,657
Actually, that was the First Division's...

486
00:40:27,658 --> 00:40:30,094
I give the credit to you.

487
00:40:31,629 --> 00:40:32,496
Please don't.

488
00:40:33,464 --> 00:40:34,931
I didn't do anything.

489
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:36,167
Yes, you did.

490
00:40:38,269 --> 00:40:39,903
- You know?
- No, I didn't.

491
00:40:39,904 --> 00:40:41,005
Yes, you did.

492
00:40:42,106 --> 00:40:43,040
You know?

493
00:40:44,141 --> 00:40:45,075
No, I didn't.

494
00:40:46,210 --> 00:40:47,211
Yes, you did.

495
00:40:47,878 --> 00:40:48,946
This is getting annoying.

496
00:40:50,080 --> 00:40:51,182
Yes, you did.

497
00:41:12,336 --> 00:41:15,606
THREE YEARS AGO

498
00:41:16,106 --> 00:41:18,776
Are you admitting
that you leaked the information?

499
00:41:19,310 --> 00:41:20,710
Would you lie like that?

500
00:41:20,711 --> 00:41:25,349
If you don't deny the suspicion,
people will assume it's true.

501
00:41:25,950 --> 00:41:27,784
You won't be able to work here.

502
00:41:27,785 --> 00:41:31,222
Will you be able to say the same thing
in front of Oda's grave?

503
00:41:31,989 --> 00:41:33,591
You won't, will you?

504
00:41:35,426 --> 00:41:36,560
Mr. Yanagi,

505
00:41:37,461 --> 00:41:39,096
stop involving yourself with me.

506
00:41:40,464 --> 00:41:43,367
Being around me will lead
to a negative outcome for you.

507
00:41:44,034 --> 00:41:47,004
It would impact your dream
of joining the First Division.

508
00:41:48,973 --> 00:41:49,940
You...

509
00:41:52,209 --> 00:41:54,678
Don't you dare give me attitude.

510
00:41:55,346 --> 00:41:59,483
I'm the one who's most upset
about you giving up your future.

511
00:42:05,222 --> 00:42:06,890
ORIGINAL STORY BY KUROMARU

512
00:42:06,891 --> 00:42:08,392
Arikino!

513
00:42:38,088 --> 00:42:39,422
I didn't steal it.

514
00:42:39,423 --> 00:42:41,925
It doesn't matter
whether you're a thief or not.

515
00:42:41,926 --> 00:42:44,928
I wonder why in the world I work
as an interpreter for the police.

516
00:42:44,929 --> 00:42:47,230
<i>I have nothing.</i>

517
00:42:47,231 --> 00:42:50,634
<i>Susumu is the same with Tien.</i>

518
00:42:51,235 --> 00:42:55,139
Do you think friendship can be restored
even after it's broken?

519
00:42:56,740 --> 00:42:57,608
Tien.

520
00:43:02,780 --> 00:43:06,250
FOUR YEARS AGO

521
00:43:08,586 --> 00:43:09,587
I see.

522
00:43:11,655 --> 00:43:13,123
It's bigger than I thought.

523
00:43:15,993 --> 00:43:17,494
It'll be small before you know it.

524
00:43:19,129 --> 00:43:19,964
Huh?

525
00:43:21,899 --> 00:43:26,403
All sorts of things
will soon fill this place, I'm sure.

526
00:43:34,979 --> 00:43:36,413
This is the smoking spot.

527
00:43:37,915 --> 00:43:42,486
Or smoking under the exhaust fan
might be acceptable as well.

528
00:43:47,024 --> 00:43:49,393
It's okay. I will quit.

529
00:43:50,361 --> 00:43:51,261
Huh?

530
00:43:52,596 --> 00:43:54,064
It's a good timing for me.

531
00:43:57,701 --> 00:44:00,070
Can I have it then?

532
00:44:03,107 --> 00:44:05,876
- You don't smoke, though.
- Who cares?

533
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:13,350
There.

534
00:44:18,022 --> 00:44:19,156
Thanks.
